    An Assignment is a list of RandomVariables and their corresponding values (Objects).

    A BayesianNetwork is a network of nodes, each of which corresponds to a random variable.

    Scanner for the Bison-generate BIFParser.

    Distribution
    Class representing a probability distribution for a single RandomVariable.
    Domain
    A Domain represents an ordered set of possible Values for a Variable.
    EnumerationInferencer
    Implements the depth-first inference by enumeration algorithm for exact inference in Bayesian networks described in AIMA Figure 14.9.
    PriorSampler
    Class implementing the Prior-Sample algorithm from AIMA Section 14.5.1.
    RandomVariable
    A RandomVariable in a BayesianNetwork has a name and a Domain of possible values.
    RejectionSamplingInferencer
    Implements the rejection sampling algorithm for approximate inference in Bayesian networks described in AIMA Figure 14.14.
    XMLBIFParser
    DOM Parser (DocumentBuilder)-based parser for XMLBIF files.
